&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a part time ward administrator based on ward D55 Healthcare of older people at the Queens Medical Centre Working 18.75 hours over 5 days Monday-Friday.&lt;br /&gt;You will be working alongside the ward manager providing high quality administration support.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Knowledge and experience of ward administration would be beneficial but not essential. A good standard of education and experience of Microsoft Office packages including a good knowledge of Word and Excel is essential. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We require an enthusiastic and conscientious team player with excellent organisational and communication skills. You will need to be able to demonstrate a clear understanding of confidentiality issues, be well motivated and reliable.&lt;br /&gt;You will also be able to prioritise workloads, use your own initiative and respond to queries within and outside the Organisation with a professional manner to Patients, relatives and staff at all levels.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAndrew RileyJob titleMatronEmail addressandrew.riley@nuh.nhs.ukTelephone number0115 9249 924Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information or to arrange an informal visit/chat, please contact Matron Andrew Riley or Sarah Mack by email: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Andrew.riley@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;sarah.mack@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or by calling 01159 249924 ext 87897&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
